  "prompt": "\"CAS PRES CHQ\" what does this SBI statement message mean?",
  "response": "The message \"CAS PRES CHQ\" on an SBI (State Bank of India) statement typically stands for \"Cash Presented Cheque.\" This means that a cheque you issued was presented for encashment, and the amount was debited from your account. If you have any further questions or need more details, feel free to ask!",
